# Keystatic GitHub auth — only needed in production (Netlify).
# Local dev uses { kind: 'local' } and writes to disk directly; no env needed.
#
# To fill these out:
#   1. Create a GitHub App: https://keystatic.com/docs/github-setup
#      (or manually via github.com/settings/apps/new)
#      - Homepage URL: https://idkstorytellingbutihavestoriestotell.netlify.app
#      - Callback URL: https://idkstorytellingbutihavestoriestotell.netlify.app/api/keystatic/github/oauth/callback
#      - Webhook URL: https://idkstorytellingbutihavestoriestotell.netlify.app/api/keystatic/github/webhook
#      - Permissions: Contents (R/W), Metadata (R), Pull requests (R/W)
#   2. Install the app on the `Triamb-Talwar/i-dont-know-storytelling` repo.
#   3. Copy Client ID + generate a Client Secret.
#   4. Generate a random 32+ char string for KEYSTATIC_SECRET (used to sign session cookies).
#   5. Add all three to Netlify -> Site settings -> Environment variables.

KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
KEYSTATIC_SECRET=

# Optional: public-facing URL used by Keystatic when constructing OAuth redirects.
# Defaults to the request's own origin, which works on Netlify.
# KEYSTATIC_URL=https://idkstorytellingbutihavestoriestotell.netlify.app
